summary:
In ancient Greek mythology, the twelve Olympians are the most important gods. They live on Mount Olympus and each have unique symbols. These gods include Zeus (with his thunderbolt), Hera, Poseidon, Demeter, Aphrodite, Athena, Artemis, Apollo, Ares, Hephaestus, Hermes, and Hestia or Dionysus.

A cool artifact, a relief sculpture from around 1st century BC-AD, shows these gods parading with their special items. It's now at the Walters Art Museum.
title: Twelve Olympians
